'''濾過裂隙'''（{{lang|en|filtration slits}}），即[[腎|腎臟]]的組成[[腎單位|腎元]]之[[腎小體|腎小體]]內的[[鮑氏囊|鮑氏囊]]上之[[足細胞|足細胞]]的"足突"叉合彼此形成"濾過裂隙"(或裂隙孔)、且裂隙極小(約為8 [[纳米|nm]])，而帶有[[負電荷|負電荷]]、大分子以及帶陰電性的[[分子|分子]]會被阻擋在外。<ref name=guyton11>{{Cite book | author=Guyton, Arthur C.; Hall, John E. | title=Textbook of Medical Physiology | year=2006 | publisher=Elsevier Saunders | location=Philadelphia | isbn=0-7216-0240-1 | pages=316–317}}</ref> 濾過裂隙可對比於[[腎小球|腎小球]][[內皮|內皮]]細胞的膜孔(fenestra)，並由"裂隙隔膜"(slit diaphragm)跨越其上。

==結構==
一些研究表明，濾過裂隙的尺寸限制了大的[[分子|分子]](比如:[[血清白蛋白|血清白蛋白]]([[直径|直径]]約為15～30[[微米|μm]]))、及細胞(比如:[[红血球|红血球]](直徑約6～8µm)和[[血小板|血小板]](直徑约2～4μm，厚0.2～1.5μm，平均體積7μm<sup>3</sup>))的通過。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Update on the glomerular filtration barrier|pages=226–232|issn=1473-6543|journal=Current Opinion in Nephrology and Hypertension|volume=18|issue=3|date=2009-5|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19374010|accessdate=2019-02-13|author=George Jarad, Jeffrey H. Miner|pmid=19374010|pmc=PMC2895306|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609020121/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19374010|dead-url=no}}</ref> 運作"濾過裂隙"的正確功能需要的蛋白質包括[[腎病蛋白|腎病蛋白]]<ref>Wartiovaara, J.; Ofverstedt, L. G. R.; Khoshnoodi, J.; Zhang, J.; Mäkelä, E.; Sandin, S.; Ruotsalainen, V.; Cheng, R. H.; Jalanko, H.; Skoglund, U.; Tryggvason, K. (2004). "Nephrin strands contribute to a porous slit diaphragm scaffold as revealed by electron tomography". Journal of Clinical Investigation 114 (10): 1475–1483. doi:10.1172/JCI22562. PMC 525744. PMID 15545998</ref>、[[KIRREL|NEPH1]](KIRREL)、[[KIRREL3|NEPH2]](KIRREL3)<ref>Neumann-Haefelin, E.; Kramer-Zucker, A.; Slanchev, K.; Hartleben, B.; Noutsou, F.; Martin, K.; Wanner, N.; Ritter, A.; Gödel, M.; Pagel, P.; Fu, X.; Müller, A.; Baumeister, R.; Walz, G.; Huber, T. B. (2010). "A model organism approach: Defining the role of Neph proteins as regulators of neuron and kidney morphogenesis". Human Molecular Genetics 19 (12): 2347–2359. doi:10.1093/hmg/ddq108. PMID 20233749</ref>、[[足蛋白|足蛋白]]，及[[CD2AP|CD2AP]]。<ref>Fukasawa, H.; Bornheimer, S.; Kudlicka, K.; Farquhar, M. G. (2009). "Slit Diaphragms Contain Tight Junction Proteins". Journal of the American Society of Nephrology 20 (7): 1491–1503. doi:10.1681/ASN.2008101117. PMC 2709684. PMID 19478094</ref>

